The Osun State Police Command has declared the duo of Solomon Adefioye Adedimeji, aka Solo Iwara and Rasheed Hamed, aka Rasheed Okoilu wanted. According to a statement signed by SP Yemisi Opalola, the Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) of the command, the Osun Command is soliciting the cooperation of the members of the public to divulge useful information as to the whereabouts of the suspects. According to the information made available by Opalola and obtained by DAILY POST on Thursday, 33-year-old Adedimeji, who is a native of Iwara in Osun State, is wanted in connection with murder, arson, ritual killing, armed robbery, rape and kidnapping. His physical description was given as, “dark complexion, white teeth, 1.75 metres tall, pointed nose, oblong head, black hair and Yoruba by tribe. “The suspect has been causing menace in Iwara and the entire Osun State. Anybody that harbours the suspect would be treated by the police as an accomplice to the crimes highlighted above.” She also revealed that the second suspect, Rasheed Okoilu hails from Ede, Osun State and is wanted for the crime of murder, arson, ritual killing, armed robbery, rape and kidnapping. “Rasheed Hamed is 35 years old, dark in complexion, white teeth, 1.75 metres tall, pointed nose, oblong head, black hair and Yoruba by tribe. “The suspect has been causing menace in Iwara and the entire Osun State. Anybody that harbours the suspect would be treated by the police as an accomplice to the crimes highlighted above,” she said. The Osun Police Command requested that useful information about their whereabouts should be forwarded to: 08067788119, 08937061958, 08123823981, 08039537995 and 08075872433. 